#import "/formatting.typ": *

= Sourdough Pizza <pizza-sourdough>

This is a thick, chewy sourdough pizza. See the original recipe here: #url(
  "https://www.thedivinechef.com/post/quick-sourdough-pizza",
).

*Warning:* This recipe is a @adv_hydration[high-hydration] recipe. Attempt at your own
peril.

#v(1em)

#columns(2)[
  #text(weight: "semibold")[Dough:]
  - 240 grams (1 cup), active sourdough starter (100% hydration)
  - 170 grams (3/4 cup), warm water
  - 40 grams (3 tbsp.) olive oil
  - 275 grams (2 1/2 cups), bread flour#footnote[~While you _can_ use all-purpose flour,
      it will not work well, because this recipe is very chewy.]
  - 5 grams (1 tsp.) salt

  #v(1em)

  #text(weight: "semibold")[Recommended toppings:]
  - Tomato sauce
  - Shredded mozarrella
  - Pickled green olives
  - Turkey pepperoni

  #v(1em)

  *Yields 1 pizza.*

  #colbreak()

  + Mix wet ingredients (incl. starter), then dry ingredients.
  + Add flour & salt. Mix until consistent, very wet.
  + Cover bowl with a damp towel. Let dough rise, 12-24 hours.
  + Preheat oven to 245°C (475°F).
  + Punch dough into pizza crust on baking sheet.
  + Bake 20-25 minutes.
  + Remove pizza crust from tray. Add water to bottom of tray. Flip dough upside-down and
    reinsert to tray.
  + Add toppings.
  + Bake another 7-10 minutes, double-checking every 2–3 minutes.
  + Let pizza sit for 5 minutes before slicing.
]
